    • Method Detail

      • createKeyEventFromCurrentState

        public static CoreKeyEventLwjgl createKeyEventFromCurrentState()
        Creates a new CoreKeyEvent using the data collected from the last call to Keyboard.poll(). It is the responsibility of the caller to call Keyboard.next() to advance to the next buffered event.
        Returns:
        the CoreKeyEventLwjgl representing this event
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the Keyboard has not yet been initialized via Keyboard.create().
